message: What do you think about CS106A after taking CS50 ?

data.message:
In my own opinion, I believe you would learn a lot more from actually coding than from studying methodology (which CS106 is actually all about) 
I wouldn't advise taking CS106 now since you're not a college student, you'd quickly lose the information since they're not really that practical for you and you'd have wasted your time.
But, if you have some free time that you don't know what to do with it, then enroll in CS106.
